  "Property developer's son Achal Bakeri branched out into manufacturing in 1988 by borrowing $1,500 from his father. \r\n",
  "Today his Bombay Stock Exchange-listed Symphony is the world's biggest producer of air coolers selling 1.2 million units annually in 60 countries. \r\n",
